# 8. まだ遠くても、いつか

Akito: Wow... I was thirstier than I realized.
Akito: It's funny how it's sometimes hard to tell how you actually are... Anyway, where can I toss this...
Toya: Akito!
Akito: Huh? What are you all doing here...?
An: You're kidding, right? We were worried sick about you!
Luka: <Sorry, Akito!>
Akito: Whoa! Luka?!
Luka: <I was actually hiding in your pocket the entire time, but I never really got the opportunity to talk to you.>
Luka: <When you decided to battle against those other performers, I rushed to find Toya...>
Akito: You did...?
Akito: I apologize for making you do that, Luka, all of you. And thank you for going out of your way to find me.
Luka: <No, that's okay. I'm just glad to see that you're safe.>
An: Also, you battled against those guys all by yourself, didn't you? You really made it out in one piece?
Akito: Yeah, I did fine. They were nothing special in the end.
Akito: I mean, we're trying to surpass RAD WEEKEND. I'm not gonna lose to the likes of them or let anything stop me from accomplishing that goal.
Kohane: You're so strong, Shinonome...
Kohane: By the way, what were they like?
Akito: Oh, so...
An: Wow... That really happened at Crawl Green?
Toya: When Akito and I first teamed up, he kept getting badgered by all these prickly customers...
Toya: Now I realize that you've been dealing with their ilk for quite a long time.
Akito: To be fair, I wasn't exactly the most pleasant person to deal with at the time. I don't blame them for what happened.
Akito: I bit off more than I could chew. Plain and simple.
Akito: Anyway, if we do get to sing at Crawl Green, I promise to put on a performance that's going to floor everyone there.
Kohane: I'll be there with you! After all, we're teammates!
Akito: Kohane...
Toya: She's right. I'll be right next to you as well. We can rewrite history, together.
An: Yeah, let's put on a show that totally erases what happened back then.
Akito: That'd be nice...
Akito: Alright, let's go blow the roof off that place.
Akito: Oh, about our next event... There's something I need to tell all of you...
Kotaro: Hey, Akito!
Kotaro: There you are... Wait, huh?! What are you guys doing here?!
Akito: A few different reasons...
Akito: Actually, Mita, sorry for ditching you back there. After making you tag along with me too...
Kotaro: No, don't mind me. I mean, just now, you...
Kotaro: Well, you seem all better now, so that's good.
Akito: I am, thanks.
Akito: Anyway, about our next event...
Akito: Taiga said he'd come and watch.
Toya: Is that true, Akito?
Kotaro: Taiga's really coming to see our event?!
Akito: Yeah! That is, if we manage to book Crawl Green...
An: Uncle Taiga, huh...? That means Arata and I have some work to do.
Kotaro: I bet Tono's gonna feel even more motivated after he hears this news.
Akito: I'm not worried about our motivation.
An: Me neither! I mean, this is probably the best Christmas present we could've asked for!
Akito: Uh, good for us...?
Kohane: Taiga's coming to see us...
Taiga: And I'm curious to find out just how far she can go if she's given that chance.
Kohane: (It'll be the first time he sees us perform after I started learning more about singing from him.)
Kohane: I need to do my best...
Taiga: Become just like him, huh...?
Taiga: I really let my mouth run back there... Now I'm starting to sound like Ken.
Taiga: I...
Nagi: Ken, Taiga...
Nagi: I have a feeling that the next generation of singers is going to help keep our dream alive...
Kotaro: Wait, Akito, I thought you were done training!
Akito: No way, dude. I've still got some stuff left to do.
Akito: My body's all warmed up, so now I've gotta get my voice ready.
Toya: Oh, in that case, I'd like to join you.
Kohane: Um, me too...
An: Then, why don't we head over to the cafe? Dad just replaced all the equipment, which made singing that much more fun!
Kotaro: Huh...?
An: Kohane and I got a chance earlier to test it all out!
Akito: Yeah, that's not a bad idea...
Toya: I agree. Also, I know it's getting late, but I'd like to join in if possible.
An: Of course you're welcome! What about you Kotaro?
Kotaro: Th-Then, I'll go too!
An: Awesome! Oh, how about we...? Race to see who gets there first!
Kohane & Toya: Yeah! Okay.
Kotaro: Wait, we're gonna run?!
Akito: They sound pretty excited...
Akito: ...
Akito: (We've got a long road ahead of us before we can surpass RAD WEEKEND. But...)
Akito: (Someday... If that person's waiting for me beyond that gigantic hurdle...)
Akito: I'm gonna succeed. No matter what it takes...
An: Akito, you coming?! You're gonna get left behind!
Akito: Yeah, wait up...!
An's Father: Once they get here, they all want to sing, huh?
An's Father: Sounds like things went more or less smoothly.
An's Father: (I wasn't sure what would happen when I heard that Akito was going to battle someone... At the same time, I knew that he wouldn't do anything rash.)
An's Father: Welcome. Oh, hello...
Owner of Crawl Green: It's been a while, Ken.
An's Father: Yes, fancy seeing you here. What can I get for you?
Owner of Crawl Green: Actually, it's about my place. It's not exactly a big deal, but this one kid's been badgering me about letting him and his friends host an event.
Owner of Crawl Green: He keeps saying, “Our show will be better than the time RADder debuted. We promise to fill this place up and completely blow the roof off.”
An's Father: Ah, you must be talking about...
Owner of Crawl Green: Yes, Arata Tono. He mentioned that your daughter's team is a part of his group.
An's Father: I see... I apologize if they've been causing you any trouble.
Owner of Crawl Green: No, that's all fine. If anything, I've been feeling a bit of nostalgia.
Owner of Crawl Green: When RADder debuted... When RAD WEEKEND happened...and became the stuff of legends...
Owner of Crawl Green: And quite a lot of time has passed since what happened with Nagi...
An's Father: ...
Owner of Crawl Green: A lot of teams have done events at my place, but none have been able to achieve the same sort of oneness that you guys did...
Owner of Crawl Green: I've become convinced that I'll never get to see an event like that again.
An's Father: Actually, you may be in for a bit of a surprise...
Owner of Crawl Green: Haha. No one's going to top you, Taiga and Nagi. Speaking of, An's team... What's their name again? Vivid BAD SQUAD?
Owner of Crawl Green: I know one of her teammates. He stank up the place a while back during this one event. I was planning on giving him a piece of my mind back then...
Owner of Crawl Green: But I hear he's gotten a lot better lately.
An's Father: He has. I can vouch for him.
An's Father: He's improved quite a lot, and I suspect he's going to keep growing.
An's Father: He really has become a good singer.
An's Father: (Nagi, Taiga...)
An's Father: (We might just get a chance to see our dream come back to life in the near future...)
